  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train 500 Activists to Fight for Lower Drug Prices</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At least 81 million Americans struggle to afford life-saving drugs. Many Americans believe prescription drugs are too expensive and prices should be lower. The Right Care Alliance (RCA)  will teach 80 clinician and patient activists in MA, FL, CO, and DC about how drug prices are set and regulated. The RCA will train them to organize against the drug companies and the middle men who set prices; and to become leaders who train at least 100 other people in their communities.</narrative>
  </description>
